## API Authentication Key
## This key must match the APP_CHAT_KEY from the backend configuration
## Used for authenticating chat requests to the backend API (server-side only)
NEXT_PRIVATE_CHAT_API_KEY="<YOUR_CHAT_API_KEY>"

## Backend API URL
## For local development: http://localhost:8080
## Backend runs on port 8080 with HTTP (no SSL in development)
NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL="http://localhost:8080"

## EmailJS Configuration
## Get these from https://dashboard.emailjs.com/
## All email sending is handled server-side via /api/send-email

## Private credentials (SECRET - server only)
NEXT_PRIVATE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID="<YOUR_SERVICE_ID>"
NEXT_PRIVATE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID="<YOUR_TEMPLATE_ID>"
NEXT_PRIVATE_EMAILJS_PRIVATE_KEY="<YOUR_PRIVATE_KEY>"

## Public key (required by EmailJS, safe to expose)
NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY="<YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY>"
